EVC().notice: Returns the address of the Ethereum Vault Connector (EVC) used by this contract.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Allow spender to access an amount of your eTokens

balanceOf(address).notice: Balance of a particular account, in eTokens

checkVaultStatus().notice: Checks the status of the vault and validates supply cap constraints.

convertToAssets(uint256).notice: Calculate amount of assets corresponding to the requested shares amount

convertToShares(uint256).notice: Calculate amount of shares corresponding to the requested assets amount

deposit(uint256,address).notice: Deposits a certain amount of assets for a receiver.

governorAdmin().notice: The address of the governor admin.

maxDeposit(address).notice: Fetch the maximum amount of assets a user can deposit

maxMint(address).notice: Fetch the maximum amount of shares a user can mint

maxRedeem(address).notice: Fetch the maximum amount of shares a user is allowed to redeem for assets

maxWithdraw(address).notice: Fetch the maximum amount of assets a user is allowed to withdraw

mint(uint256,address).notice: Mints a certain amount of shares for a receiver.

previewDeposit(uint256).notice: Calculate an amount of shares that would be created by depositing assets

previewMint(uint256).notice: Calculate an amount of assets that would be required to mint requested amount of shares

previewRedeem(uint256).notice: Calculate the amount of assets that will be transferred when redeeming requested amount of shares

previewWithdraw(uint256).notice: Calculate the amount of shares that will be burned when withdrawing requested amount of assets

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: Redeems a certain amount of shares for a receiver.

setGovernorAdmin(address).notice: Sets a new governor admin for the vault.

setSupplyCap(uint16).notice: Sets the supply cap for the vault.

supplyCap().notice: Returns the raw supply cap value as a uint16.

supplyCapResolved().notice: Returns the resolved supply cap as a uint256.

totalAssets().notice: Returns the total assets of the vault.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfers a certain amount of shares to a recipient.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfers a certain amount of shares from a sender to a recipient.

withdraw(uint256,address,address).notice: Withdraws a certain amount of assets for a receiver.
